  },
  {
    "id": "70a92691-3603-4c94-8448-c98592c32e58",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "2519cce2-6262-4016-9853-7382336242af",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "You can also point out/mention any other document within your Organization. This is very helpful as you want someone to see also connected somehow documents (or you do it just for yourself to have in mind these connections)",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "3fc95949-2ff0-4797-a06b-4016951aae58",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In this case you just use @ and dropdown list will appear",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "a6f0afef-a41d-4310-af35-1578efd235e4",
    "type": "image",
    "props": {
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left",
      "name": "335.png",
      "url": "onboardingContent:10-how-to-mention-someone-or-something/335.png",
      "caption": "",
      "showPreview": true,
      "previewWidth": 512
    },
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "345c6f78-cf17-4e70-a278-09627517d3bf",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "36b3c2d6-bd4b-4915-8a29-ea9cf74edde0",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and you just choose a document you would like to mention/inlude in current document.",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "be5ae0f0-9ca2-488a-a8e7-4b24ca79264a",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "d779b5d9-146b-4364-bc19-d9d02cb14aa0",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In Fundamento list of contents is called a \"Structure\", since in fact it is the structure of your document and you are able to create it in a planned way.",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "14743fd6-4a62-4f54-ba3a-6f937a3a563a",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Any time when you click \"Turn into\" (as you click six dots symbol on the blank field on the left side of the paragraph) and choose \"Heading1\", \"Heading2\", \"Heading3\", this will be reflected in the structure of your document since \"Heading\" is a part of the list of content.",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "9d4ead84-c239-45f3-873d-a2150e807132",
    "type": "image",
    "props": {
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left",
      "name": "Headings.jpg",
      "url": "onboardingContent:10-how-to-mention-someone-or-something/headings.jpg",
      "caption": "",
      "showPreview": true,
      "previewWidth": 101
    },
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "ba231ae6-4c44-4467-9b27-50448a77f041",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "6ae547dd-f0d5-4fb0-98ae-9b10b93e7f68",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "And reversedly - as some part of the text is already a header (and appears in the Structure of the document) and you don't want it to be in the list of content, you just change a \"Heading' for a \"Paragraph\"",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "36b6021e-c30f-430e-9d20-fb13c851fde3",
    "type": "image",
    "props": {
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left",
      "name": "Paragraph.jpg",
      "url": "onboardingContent:10-how-to-mention-someone-or-something/paragraph.jpg",
      "caption": "",
      "showPreview": true,
      "previewWidth": 129
    },
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "ace64c32-9c40-4c93-8d34-8b438db110e4",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and then part of the text will be no more part of the list of contents.",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "fee06b0e-c8dd-442a-8abc-b4d29f1240bf",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
